"It pours a chill hazed amber under a 1” white foam cap with a very slight amber tint. The nose is faint with a light wisp of grape, light very ripe fruit, pine and light sugars. You first notice the toffee aromas, then grape to chardonnay followed by pine. A thread of light toffee runs all the way through the palate supported by light fruit with some piney bitterness on the finish. Nicely balanced. It has above average carbonation and medium to just below on the body."
