"Smells like a marzen.  Taste is big toasted malt, light chocolate, and light woodsy hops.  Taste is like a mix between a marzen and a pale ale, with not as much hops as I usually associate with a pale ale.  Not a bad beer, but when I heard these two breweries were collaborating, I was expecting much more.  A pass for me in the future."
