"Pours a hazy, brown/pink color.  2/3 inch head of an off-white color.  Great retention and great lacing.  Smells of citrus hops, hint of spice, hint of alcohol, sweet malt, hint of pine, and a hint of yeast.  Fits the style of an American Strong Ale.  Mouth feel is sharp and crisp, with an average carbonation level.  Tastes of sweet malt, hint of sugar, hint of caramel malt, hint of yeast, hops, and a hint of fruit.  Overall, good appearance, aroma, complexity, and blend, but the body is underwhelming."
""
