""
"i had hoped for a much more adventurous recipe when i saw these guys were collaborating. a strong pale to ipa on the hops front, but more bitter than flavor there, over a unique and robust autumnal grain base, copper and wheaty, fuller bodied, and balanced the way an esb might be. nothing new in terms of style overall though, i really thought they would get more creative to mark such a momentous occasion, so i am let down by that. the beer though, as unambitious as it is, is very good. full flush warming body, aggressive bubbles, and a nice tacky oily hop character in the finish. its big in flavor, and its perfect for this time of year. i have no issue with the beer at all, i just had hoped for a lot more with these two giants getting together. maybe next time..."
